  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Audit Associate/Senior",
  "description": "<p>Key Responsibilities:<br>\n<br>\n- Lead audit engagements of various sizes<br>\n<br>\n- Collaborate with team members for timely completion and high-quality audit work<br>\n<br>\n- Manage client relationships and expectations<br>\n<br>\n- Guide and coach junior staff<br>\n<br>\n- Develop and execute audit plans, programs and verification<br>\n<br>\nSpecific Tasks:<br>\n<br>\n- Obtain understanding of clients' businesses and develop tailored audit strategies<br>\n<br>\n- Prepare and document planning procedures<br>\n<br>\n- Perform audit tests of controls and substantive procedures to ensure that these assignments are planned, executed, documented and concluded based on the relevant professional standards<br>\n<br>\n- Address assertions such as existence, completeness, rights, obligations, valuation, accuracy, presentation, and disclosure<br>\n<br>\n- Prepare recommendation letter to client to improve control and enhance business efficiency<br>\n<br>\n- Assist in due diligence, grant audit, compilation and any other special audit services<br>\n<br>\n- Work closely with Audit Manager/Audit Partner<br>\n<br>\nRequirements:<br>\n<br>\n- Degree or Diploma in Accountancy, ACCA, CA or equivalent professional qualification<br>\n<br>\n- 2+ years of relevant audit experience (preferable)<br>\n<br>\n- Strong technical knowledge of accounting and auditing standards<br>\n<br>\n- Strong communication and analytical skills<br>\n<br>\n- Proactive, committed, and team-oriented<br>\n<br>\n- Ability to work independently and manage time effectively<br>\n<br>\nWhat We Offer:<br>\n<br>\n- Opportunity for professional growth and development<br>\n<br>\n- Challenging and fulfilling career advancement<br>\n<br>\n- Dynamic working environment and practices<br>\n<br>\n- Ongoing training and support<br>\n<br>\n- Unlimited pantry access<br>\n<br>\n- Competitive compensation package</p>",
